definition.value: A dihydroxybenzoate that is the conjugate base of 3,5-dimethylorsellinic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Any oxygenated derivative of C22 polyunsaturated fatty acids, such as docosapentaenoic acid (DPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA).
Any saturated fatty acid anion carrying one or more hydroxy substituents.
A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as pentadecanoyl.
A class of carbonyl compound encompassing dicarboxylic acids and any derivatives obtained by substitution of either one or both of the carboxy hydrogens.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 20:1 in which the acyl group is located at position 1.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 20:3 in which the acyl group is located at position 2.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 22:4 in which the docosatetraenoyl group is located at position 1.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 22:5 in which the acyl group is located at position 1.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 22:6 in which the docosahexaenoyl group is located at position 1.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 22:6 in which the acyl group is specified as docosahexaenoyl and is located at position 2.
A lysophosphatidylcholine in which the acyl group has a fully saturated C19 chain and is attached to the glycero moiety at either position 1 or 2.
A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as nonadecanoyl.
A monoalkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl group contains 18 carbons and no double bonds.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the fatty acyl group contains 18 carbons and 2 double bonds.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of pentacosanoic acid with the amino group of sphingosine.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 43 with 1 double bond.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of glycerol 2-phosphate.
A hydrate that is the tetrahydrate form of sodium glycerol 2-phosphate.
An organic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and glycolate ions.
A hydrate that is the monohydrate form of sodium metavanadate.
An organic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and methoxyacetate ions.
A hydrate that is the tetrahydrate form of sodium molybdate.
An organic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and octanoate ions.
An organic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and orotate ions.
An inorganic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and perchlorate ions.
An organic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and propionate ions.
A hydrate that is the decahydrate form of trisodium phosphate.
A hydrate that is the nonahydrate form of sodium silicate.
An organic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and stearate ions.
An organic sodium salt comprising equal numbers of sodium and syringate ions.
A methoxybenzoate that is the conjugate base of syringic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
An inorganic sodium salt composed of sodium and thiosulfate ions in a 2:1 ratio.
An indol-3-yl carboxylic acid that is 3-(1H-indol-3-yl)butanoic acid substituted at positions 2 and 3 by hydroxy and methyl groups respectively.
Any member of the class of benzoquinones that is 1,4-benzoquinone or its C-substituted derivatives.
A member of the class of dihydroxybenzoic acids that is o-orsellinic acid carrying two additional methyl substituents at positions 3 and 5.
A naphthoquinone in which the oxo groups of the quinone moiety are at positions 1 and 4 of the parent naphthalene ring.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of hyaluronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An alkane that is hexane in which the two methylene hydrogens at position 3 have been replaced by methyl groups.
A nucleobase analogue that is uracil substituted at position 5 by a 4,5-dihydroxypentyl group.
A branched alkane consisting of decane bearing three methyl substituents at positions 2, 6 and 7.
A member of the class of 1-benzofurans that is a lignan obtained by cyclodimerisation of ferulic acid. It is isolated from several plants including spearmint.
A member of the class of 1-benzofurans that is a lignan obtained by cyclodimerisation of ferulic acid.
A member of the class of phenazines that is 1,4,10,10a-tetrahydrophenazine substituted at position 1 by a carboxy group (the 1R,10aS-diastereomer).
A member of the class of phenazines that is (10aS)-10,10a-dihydrophenazine substituted at position 1 by a carboxy group
An lysophosphatidylcholine derived from epoxidation across the double bond of 1-O-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.
An lysophosphatidylcholine derived from epoxidation across the double bond of 1-O-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.
A branched alkane consisting of tridecane bearing a single methyl substituent at position 4.
A branched alkane consisting of dodecane bearing three methyl substituents at positions 2, 6 and 11.
